title: absolutely wonderful place with some of the nicest and helpful people working there.
review:
bathroom the top of the wall in the bathroom is open so bugs are able to easily get into the bathroom also if it is raining outside the it will be wet inside maybe adding a screen or glass partition should be considered 
the location it is a little far from the downtown area there was road work going on so you have to go around adding maybe 2030 minutes to the trip it is quiet but that is a good thing if youre looking to relax the restaurant and room service ends at 10301100 pm so if you are looking for a late night bite youre out of luck there is however a 24hour convenience store not too far from the property

despite these things i still think this place is wonderful this place is amazing we enjoyed every moment of our stay the room was huge clean and well maintained the bathroom was large with a big soaker tub in the middle we arranged for the flower bath upon arrival and the flowers were beautifully arranged however by the time we went to get in all of the water had somehow drained out of the tub i called the front desk and someone was immediately sent to the room after informing the supervisor the gentleman and young woman from housekeeping cleaned out the tub and set back up the flower tub i was so impressed with how quickly they worked to set the bath back up i feel so bad that i dont remeber their names because they deserve a special shout out all day breakfast so we were able to sleep in is a wonderful perk offered at this hotel the breakfast menu has a ton of options and our meals were so tasty and always freshly prepared huge shout out to the staff at elys kitchen especially nyoman vopi and lingnam im not sure if thats the correct spelling of his name made our afternoonevening dining experiences truly memorable 
there is a free shuttle that takes you into the downtown area it makes trips hourly and the last shuttle back to the property is at 9 pm
everyone that works there is so friendly and helpful ive never met such nice people

title: perfect stay in ubud, i’ll be recommending this hotel to everyone i know.
review:
nothing everything at the property was amazing from the moment we arrived at the hotel until we checked out the hotel staff were friendly and welcoming and greeted us with a smile at all times the staff were extremely helpful and respectful and ensured that we received excellent service throughout our stay including the laundry service breakfast early in the morning and recommendations to local restaurants hotel and restaurant staff provided quick service

we stayed in the forest view hotel room and the room was spacious with a lovely bath and lovely patio area with a gorgeous view of the greenery around us our hotel room was clean and tidy every day to an excellent standard as an added extra the staff left information about ubud in our room each day and cookies too as well as refreshed the bottles of water tea and the mini fridge 

dedy the supervisor as well as the other staff frequently asked about our stay and provided helpful information including helping us rent a moped for the day as needed and was very friendly and welcoming 

the pool was well maintained fairly big and had a lovely view as well as having sun beds to relax on and offering pool side service for food and drinks 

when we were leaving the hotel staff went the extra mile to help us with our luggage and gave us a little present as a gift for our stay 

the hotel also offered a free photography session in their lovely gardens we didnt get around to using this due to time limits 

on arrival i also received a whatsapp message from the hotel letting me know that i could use whatsapp to ask any questions and get in contact with reception staff

title: it was perfect stay for my family, my family had great time indeed.
review:
not much to be honest i need to be picky to complain but i do want to share points for improvement if adiwana can look into this 
1 there was no disabled pathway which makes it very difficult for the stroller or luggage i do suggest the owners look into this seriously all their staffs are super friendly hence helping to carry luggage all the way to your room and back  forth its pity for me see the staffs on their daily activity they need to carry everything on their shoulder which is very heavy i really hope the owner could make improvement which can be friendlier for disabled luggage stroller and for their own staffs daily activities 
2 while the internet was super fast the tv channels are quite bad lucky we got out android dongle to plug  play to enjoy music and online streaming 
3 location is 2km away from ubud center the buggy services operating on selective days  period its shut by 530 pm so we use the ridehailing app to commute hope they can improvise here my first experience with adiwana was in nusa penida their services are really great awesome breakfast choice nice and spacious room set up hence i decided to stay in ubud with them for 4nights it was an amazing stay with aunagi suites staffs are full of smiles and were able to accommodate all our requests we had 2 forest rooms connected 1 kingbaby cot and 2 twin beds all was well set up with welcoming pastries 
its a nice honeymoon spot they have an allday breakfast 67 fix choices but very tasty and delicious concept and you can order it anytime  anywhere you wish my kids enjoyed the kids friendly pool at 13m without our observation and inroom bathtub almost every day 
it was a fantastic experience and for sure we will return but maybe try different adiwana location selection

title: pleasant & comfortable…..but falls short of its high rating.
review:
unfortunately we had an issue with our initial room there was a very deep and engrained musty mouldy smell that we tried to initially overlook but was so powerful we had to request a room change after our first night we dont complain ever thats how bad it was they moved us the following night to a new room which was fine but it put a really dampener on our stay and affected my nostrils for a few days 

i think this hotel was worth its high rating 5 years ago but is now unfortunately looking quite old and tired in places every room needs a refurbishment 

having the open plan toilet and shower within the bedroom wasnt a vibe that really appealed to us not ideal if you prefer more privacy in that respect 

road closure due to landslide means a long diversion to centre of ubud roughly1530 minutes depending on traffic its a real shame as the hotel is perfectly situated if the road wasnt damaged had we known of this closure prior to booking we may well have booked elsewhere judging by the extent of the damage to the road it doesnt look like it will be repaired anytime soon they have put on a free shuttle bus into the centre which is great but could be more frequent and run later good sized room 
massive bed
comfortable bed 
good balcony 
pool area was great 
free mini bar was a nice touch 
breakfast was delicious 
staff were very friendly 
rooms were always cleaned to a high standard

title: our 3 worst days in bali
review:
i cant understand how they have such high scores dont expect anything different from a 2star hotel the hotel is located 30min walking from ubud but there is no safe walking path to reach it while there is a shuttle available at specific times during the day these limited hours can be quite restrictive especially in the evenings you may find yourself confined to the hotel

while the hotel boasts a peaceful pool with a forest view securing a sun lounger can be quite a challenge the hotel offers minimal activities leaving you with little to do other than sitting in the uneventful lobby the restaurant despite its lofty ratings disappoints in terms of food quality with a monotonous breakfast menu

unfortunately the worst part of our stay was the room we had booked a more expensive club room and were presented with a room that looked nothing like the photos online all the furniture fixtures and essentially everything in the room appeared old and dirty it took us several days to get used to this situation while its normal to encounter mosquitoes and ants in the ubud region we certainly didnt expect to find cockroaches in the room on our last day we were shocked to discover a cockroach crawling near our towels at the edge of the sink whats more the room lacked even a hanger to hang our towels so we had to place them on the countertop even the air conditioning control seemed like it hadnt been cleaned in years on the first day we had to clean everything we needed to touch in the room ourselves all the towels appeared worn and the bed linens had permanent stains

these are just a few of the issues that come to mind our experience was so disappointing that we requested to check out the following day and asked for a refund of the remaining days of our stay after speaking to the hotel manager it took exactly 15 days to receive a response since we had only one day left we decided to tough it out we found the staff to be friendly a common trait in many bali hotels our heartfelt thanks go to the shuttle drivers who were exceptionally helpful they are the sole positive memory well take from our stay at this hotel it would be much better if lobby team sent less marketing messages on whatsapp

title: great stay and unbeatable location on the outskirts of ubud
review:
just to put some snag i do not understand why hotels in bali have adopted the european custom of putting the duvet on the bed temperature at night doesnt go down from 24 degrees so we had to ask for an extra sheet to get rid of the duvet and be able to sleep with the breeze from the air conditioner without getting hot or cold we enjoyed a great stay at adiwana unagi suites hotel the quiet location and a little away from the center of ubud is perfect to escape the infernal traffic of the city also its location makes it easy to travel from ubud to the main tourist destinations north and east of the island as the traffic from the center is avoided

the facilities are beautiful and wellkept the tropical garden with the night singing of frogs and geckos the infinity pool facing the jungle where we could see several squirrels crawling up the coconut trees while we bathed 

the restaurant offers a good selection of balinese and international dishes prepared with great taste like the different choices of the very generous breakfast on demand with dishes so nice that they are sad to eat its too abundant but what you dont eat you can order to take away and take it in the middle of the morning during excursions

all staff are very professional and very attentive to guests who are always greeted and greeted with a smile even if they have to interrupt what they are doing balinese hospitality in pure condition

the hotel suggested us to wayan as a driver and it was a great experience he was very patient with us as we already knew what we wanted to see and when but provided his local recommendations it was funny because we showed him places that were not crowded which i did not know her english is quite limited but more than makes up for it with her attitude

we relaxed in the spa on our last night with a couples massage ideal to recover from a tiring intense and unequalled trip

title: great hotel that left warm memories of ubud
review: when checking out extra services and goods that we did not buy were added to the final bill for the room they added laundry and a couple of snacks in the minibar but after talking to the girl at the reception everything was removed without any problems and an updated reduced bill was provided lets hope that there was just a mistake however we advise you to keep all receipts from the hotel until the moment of checkout and recount all the money on the spot this applies not only to the hotel but to the entire island as a whole since at the airport when we paid for the visa on arrival we were given less change than we should have when we paid attention to this the girl began to smile and said that she was mistaken my wife went to the hotel for a foot massage she was very unhappy since the cost was inflated and the specialist himself sat on the phone every 2 minutes it is better to try a salon outside the hotel my wife and i vacationed in november during the rainy season the hotel staff is very friendly if any questions arose they quickly tried to resolve them we ordered a bike through the hotel for a couple of days  it was delivered within 10 minutes you could separately write a wish  request  question in wa they answered quickly and to the point one day we came to the hotel from the market with a full bag of fruit as soon as we saw it at the reception they immediately offered to cut them and 10 minutes later they brought a whole plate of cut and peeled fruit to the room every day they brought treats in the form of a saucer with cookies to the room it seems like a small thing but nice i liked the open terrace on the top floor of the building where you can play sports or just contemplate the beautiful views of the surrounding jungle the restaurant at the hotel is excellent large selection of dishes and delicious  breakfasts are large they are included in the room rate there was a choice from the menu of the proposed dishes in addition to the dish they served juice coffee  tea a plate of fruit croissants  dinner was from the menu like in a regular restaurant everything was tasty and a lot the territory of the hotel is small but quite clean and cozy wifi works great throughout the hotel every day according to the schedule free transport from the hotel and back to the central street of ubud leaves it takes about 10 minutes to get to the central street of ubud about 2530 minutes to walk the street where the hotel is located is quiet and not busy there are restaurants nearby in general we really liked the hotel and we are definitely ready to recommend it
